## Why is GAM sometimes better (logpep en simulations and sometimes worse (medsweep) than Distinct)?
Hypothesis: in medsweep -> all data is set to an equal range -> distribution changes are occuring on smaller range -> smoother sometimes has problems with oversmoothing (can't model the changes on small scale) (see example of peak difference with bimodal simulations)
